<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="383" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[816,1429,971,1850]" pageId="13" pageNumber="383">
A single adult male specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Setzer" authorityYear="1971" box="[1267,1428,971,997]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Laephotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="botswanae">
<emphasis box="[1267,1428,971,997]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="383">L. botswanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from the lower slopes (ca. 
<quantity box="[1308,1386,1005,1031]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" unit="m" value="550.0">550 m</quantity>
) of Mount Mabu (MNHG 1971.009). Identification was based on a principal component analysis of cranial measurements with the dataset from 
<bibRefCitation author="KEARNEY, T. C. &amp; E. C. SEAMARK" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" pagination="71 - 87" refId="ref13866" refString="KEARNEY, T. C., and E. C. SEAMARK. 2005. Morphometric analysis of cranial and external characters of Laephotis Thomas, 1901 (Mammalia: Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae) from southern Africa. Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 42: 71 - 87." type="journal article" year="2005">Kearney and Seamark (2005)</bibRefCitation>
. The Mount Mabu specimen fell clearly within specimens attributed by 
<bibRefCitation author="KEARNEY, T. C. &amp; E. C. SEAMARK" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" pagination="71 - 87" refId="ref13866" refString="KEARNEY, T. C., and E. C. SEAMARK. 2005. Morphometric analysis of cranial and external characters of Laephotis Thomas, 1901 (Mammalia: Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae) from southern Africa. Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 42: 71 - 87." type="journal article" year="2005">Kearney and Seamark (2005)</bibRefCitation>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Setzer" authorityYear="1971" box="[1050,1208,1210,1236]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Laephotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="botswanae">
<emphasis box="[1050,1208,1210,1236]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="383">L. botswanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(data not shown). Therefore this specimen vouches for a new distribution record for 
<collectingCountry box="[998,1156,1278,1304]" name="Mozambique" pageId="13" pageNumber="383">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
, not having previously been recorded from the country (
<bibRefCitation author="VAN CAKENBERGHE, V. &amp; E. C. J. SEAMARK" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" refId="ref15131" refString="VAN CAKENBERGHE, V., and E. C. J. SEAMARK. 2008. African Chiroptera Report 2008. African Chiroptera Project, Pretoria. www. africanbats. org" type="book" year="2008">Van Cakenberghe and Seamark, 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="MONADJEM, A. &amp; P. J. TAYLOR &amp; F. P. D. COTTERILL &amp; M. C. SCHOEMAN" box="[1073,1359,1347,1373]" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" refId="ref14234" refString="MONADJEM, A., P. J. TAYLOR, F. P. D. COTTERILL, and M. C. SCHOEMAN. 2010. Bats of Southern and Central Africa: a biogeographic and taxonomic synthesis. University of the Witwatersrand, Johannesburg, 596 pp." type="book" year="2010">
Monadjem 
<emphasis box="[1212,1276,1347,1373]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="383">et al.</emphasis>
, 2010
</bibRefCitation>
). The paucity of museum records for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Setzer" authorityYear="1971" box="[1206,1366,1381,1407]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Laephotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="botswanae">
<emphasis box="[1206,1366,1381,1407]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="383">L. botswanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
suggests that this species is rare throughout its range across Southern Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="TAYLOR, P. J." box="[1106,1262,1449,1475]" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" refId="ref14912" refString="TAYLOR, P. J. 2000. Bats of Southern Africa. Guide to biology, identification and conservation. University of Natal Press, Pietermaritzburg, 206 pp." type="book" year="2000">Taylor, 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="KEARNEY, T. C. &amp; E. C. SEAMARK" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" pagination="71 - 87" refId="ref13866" refString="KEARNEY, T. C., and E. C. SEAMARK. 2005. Morphometric analysis of cranial and external characters of Laephotis Thomas, 1901 (Mammalia: Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae) from southern Africa. Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 42: 71 - 87." type="journal article" year="2005">Kearney and Seamark, 2005</bibRefCitation>
). However, the species has been commonly recorded throughout southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1339,1429,1517,1543]" name="Malawi" pageId="13" pageNumber="383">Malawi</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="HAPPOLD, D. C. D. &amp; M. HAPPOLD &amp; J. E. HILL" box="[824,1073,1551,1577]" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" pagination="337 - 414" refId="ref13570" refString="HAPPOLD, D. C. D., M. HAPPOLD, and J. E. HILL. 1987. The bats of Malawi. Mammalia, 51: 337 - 414." type="journal article" year="1987">
Happold 
<emphasis box="[935,988,1551,1577]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="383">et al</emphasis>
., 1987
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="HAPPOLD, D. C. D. &amp; M. HAPPOLD" box="[1086,1424,1551,1577]" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" pagination="89 - 114" refId="ref13529" refString="HAPPOLD, D. C. D., and M. HAPPOLD. 1989. The bats (Chiroptera) of Malawi, central Africa: checklist and keys for identification. Nyala, 14: 89 - 114." type="journal article" year="1989">Happold and Happold, 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="HAPPOLD, M. &amp; D. C. D. HAPPOLD" box="[816,878,1585,1611]" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" pagination="805 - 836" refId="ref13605" refString="HAPPOLD, M., and D. C. D. HAPPOLD. 1997. New records of bats (Chiroptera: Mammalia) from Malawi, east-central Africa, with an assessment of their status and conservation. Journal of Natural History, 31: 805 - 836." type="journal article" year="1997">1997</bibRefCitation>
), including numerous records from lowland forest fragments around the base of Mount 
<collectingRegion box="[1324,1425,1620,1646]" country="Malawi" name="Mulanje" pageId="13" pageNumber="383">Mulanje</collectingRegion>
, only ca. 
<quantity box="[917,991,1654,1680]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" unit="km" value="60.0">60 km</quantity>
away from Mount Mabu (M. Curran and M. Kopp, unpublished data). Hence, the discovery of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Setzer" authorityYear="1971" box="[904,1066,1722,1748]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Laephotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="383" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="botswanae">
<emphasis box="[904,1066,1722,1748]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="383">L. botswanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1116,1271,1722,1748]" name="Mozambique" pageId="13" pageNumber="383">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
close to the 
<collectingCountry box="[816,906,1756,1782]" name="Malawi" pageId="13" pageNumber="383">Malawi</collectingCountry>
border was not surprising.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[816,1429,971,1850]" pageId="13" pageNumber="383">Field measurements: FA (adult male) 35.2 (1), BM (adult male) 6 (1).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
